	<td bgcolor="#404070" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ><img src="images/icons/icon1.gif" border="0" alt=""> <b>Gold Pin</b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >Just for more info on the Gold Pin charm, it dropped in Torgiran Mines off a chump Troll mob (across the bridge on the Nadox side).  ie: when you zone into the Mines from Nadox, a random troll there added on us by accident & we killed it.  I think we just got lucky off the loot table since it DEFINATELY wasn't a named/special mob.<br />
<br />
Also, to clarify, the Gold Pin only counts your total VALUE of coin, regardless of what denomination it's in.  ie:<br />
<br />
5360pp = AC 4 STA +8 MANA +23 MR +5<br />
<br />
5360pp = 53600 gold = 536000 silver = 5360000 copper<br />
<br />
you can carry any type/combination, as long as the "plat" value is >5360.<br />
<br />
I know Lucy says "Charm:Gold" or whatevers.  it works off any/all coin types.</font></p>
	
