	<td bgcolor="#303070" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" ><img src="images/icons/icon1.gif" border="0" alt=""> <b></b></font>
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >Charm of Brotherhood needs some clarification.  It infact does not have any stats when you are not grouped with another of your class, but only adds 1ac 5hp 5mana 2mr per each additional Sk (or whatever class you may have this on) in your group.  Thus solo or grouped with a shaman, I get no stats out of it.  Grouped with another SK, I get 1ac 5hp 5mana 2mr, with two I get 2ac 10hp 10mana 4mr, etc.<br />
<br />
Now I just have to figure out why in the hell I'd ever group with multiple SKs in any type of real situation... and if the extra stats would even be a blessing in that situation.<br />
<br />
Blah.  In short, this is quite possibly the worst of all charms.</font></p>
	
